						               													<description>La Reconquista is a tactical game system with generic units which simulates the great battles of the middle ages in the Iberian Peninsula from 8th to 15th century between christian and muslim units.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Each player receives activation points to move chosen units during their impulse turn and attack. &amp;#10;The different types of infantry and cavalry units include : Ridautas/Suhada, Almogavars/Mugawir, Aloers/Raxala, Hueste, Crossbowmen, Mesnada Real/Zani, Abid, Riders/Fursan, Mounted crossbowmen/Guzz, Adalides/Gara, Orders/Ribat. 15 cards add special modifications to the game.&amp;#10;A player wins by either eliminating all enemy units or by capturing 5 or more points of enemy banner markers.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;30 battle scenarios are included :&amp;#10;1. Guadalete 711, &amp;#10;2. Gormaz 917, &amp;#10;3. Simancas 939,&amp;#10;4. Matabous 985, &amp;#10;5. Quart 1094, &amp;#10;6. Bairen 1097,&amp;#10;7. Qutanda 1120, &amp;#10;8. Portopi 1229, &amp;#10;9. Zalaca 1086,&amp;#10;10. Alarcos 1195, &amp;#10;11. Ucl&amp;eacute;s 1108, &amp;#10;12. Alcoraz 1096,&amp;#10;13. Maria 1118, &amp;#10;14. Martorell 1114, &amp;#10;15. Las Navas de Tolosa 1212,&amp;#10;16. Moclin 1279, &amp;#10;17. Salado 1340, &amp;#10;18. Higueruela 1431,&amp;#10;19. Poitiers (France 732), &amp;#10;20. Roncesvalles 719, 21. Muret (France 1213),&amp;#10;22. Nicopolis (Bulgary 1396), &amp;#10;23. Aulax (Turkey 1303), &amp;#10;24. Mount Taurus (Turkey 1304),&amp;#10;25. Apros (Greece 1305), &amp;#10;26. Cefis (Greece 1311), &amp;#10;27. Covadonga 717,&amp;#10;28. Clavijo 844, &amp;#10;29. Calata&amp;ntilde;azor 1001, &amp;#10;30. Fraga 1134.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Rules adaptation are included to play with figures.&amp;#10;Distances in the map and the number of troops per unit strength are not indicated in the rules.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
